entries.title: Israel's Ben Gvir orders police to take down Palestinian flags, testing limits of his authority
entries.description: Itamar Ben Gvir, Israel's new hard-right national security minister, has ordered police to remove any Palestinian flag flown in public, arguing that displaying it shows "identification with terrorism."

entries.title: Ukrainians mark somber Orthodox Christmas in Bakhmut; shelling goes on
entries.description: The shelter was jammed with people on the eve of Orthodox Christmas.

entries.title: Kyiv dismisses Russia's claim hundreds of Ukrainian soldiers killed in Kramatorsk attack
entries.description: Ukrainian officials on Sunday dismissed Moscow's claim that a large number of Kyiv's soldiers were killed in a Russian attack last week in Kramatorsk, eastern Ukraine.

entries.title: Chinese military stages large-scale military exercises around Taiwan
entries.description: China sent 28 warplanes across the median line of the Taiwan Strait on Sunday as Beijing conducted its first large-scale military exercises around the island this year, Taiwan's Defense Ministry said.

entries.title: US Coast Guard returns 273 migrants intercepted off Florida Coast to Cuba
entries.description: The US Coast Guard says it repatriated 273 Cuban migrants Sunday after intercepting a number of boats off the Florida coast on New Year's Eve and New Year's Day.
